# Taste Skill v2 (Auto-loaded)

The full skill specification lives at:

```
.agents/skills/design-taste-frontend/SKILL.md
```

When this rule is active, treat the contents of that file as the binding spec for any UI work in this workspace. Key invariants to enforce:

## Dials (default: VARIANCE 8 / MOTION 6 / DENSITY 4)

Override per project. For data-dense dashboards, prefer VARIANCE 4-6, MOTION 2-4, DENSITY 6-8.

## Hard Bans (Section 9 — AI Tells)

- ZERO em-dash (`—`) anywhere in visible UI: headlines, eyebrows, pills, body, quotes, attribution, captions, buttons, alt text.
- NO section-numbering eyebrows (`00 / INDEX`, `001 · Capabilities`).
- NO version labels in hero (`V0.6`, `BETA`, `INVITE-ONLY`) unless brief is a launch.
- NO decorative dots before nav items / list rows (only when conveying real semantic state).
- NO photo-credit captions as decoration (`Field study no. 12 · Ines Caetano`).
- NO decorative text strips at hero bottom (`BRAND. MOTION. SPATIAL.`).
- NO scroll cues (`Scroll`, `↓ scroll`, `Scroll to explore`).
- NO version footers on marketing pages.
- NO locale / city-name / time / weather strips for non-globally-distributed briefs.
- NO Jane Doe / Acme / SmartFlow placeholder names.
- NO Inter as default font. Use Geist, Plus Jakarta Sans, Cabinet Grotesk, Satoshi, or brand-appropriate sans with full Vietnamese diacritic coverage.
- NO 3 equal-card feature rows. Use zig-zag, asymmetric, or scroll-snap alternative.
- NO fake product UI built from `<div>` rectangles.
- NO hand-rolled SVG icons. Use Phosphor / HugeIcons / Radix / Tabler.
- NO `window.addEventListener('scroll')` — use Motion `useScroll()`, GSAP ScrollTrigger, IntersectionObserver, or CSS scroll-driven animations.

## Hard Rules (Section 4)

- Color Consistency Lock: ONE accent across the whole page. Lock it. Audit every component.
- Shape Consistency Lock: ONE corner-radius system. Pick 8/12/16/pill and stick to it.
- Button Contrast Check: every CTA passes WCAG AA (4.5:1 body, 3:1 large text).
- Hero Discipline: headline ≤ 2 lines, subtext ≤ 20 words AND ≤ 4 lines, CTAs visible without scroll, font scale planned around image.
- Eyebrow Restraint: max 1 eyebrow per 3 sections (hero counts as 1). Mechanical check: count `uppercase tracking` instances ≤ ceil(sectionCount / 3).
- Italic Descender Clearance: italic words with `y g j p q` need `leading-[1.1]` minimum + `pb-1` reserve.
- Bento Cell Count: N items = exactly N cells. No empty middle or trailing cells.
- Page Theme Lock: ONE theme (light / dark / auto). No mid-page light/dark flips.
- Section-Layout-Repetition Ban: across 8 sections, at least 4 different layout families.
- Zigzag Alternation Cap: max 2 consecutive image+text-split sections.
- Split-Header Ban: do not use "left big headline + right small explainer paragraph" as section header. Stack vertically instead.
- No Duplicate CTA Intent: only one label per CTA intent (e.g., only one "contact" CTA per page).
- Long lists (>5 items) need a different UI component: 2-col grid, card-per-spec, tabs, scroll-snap pills, marquee, carousel.

## Motion Discipline (Section 5)

- Animate ONLY `transform` and `opacity`. Never `top`, `left`, `width`, `height`.
- Hardware acceleration: `will-change: transform` sparingly, only on actively animating elements.
- Reduced motion: MANDATORY for anything `MOTION_INTENSITY > 3`. Wrap in `useReducedMotion()` (Motion) or `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` (CSS).
- Motion library: `motion/react` (the rebrand of Framer Motion). GSAP only for full-page scrolltelling.
- DO NOT mix GSAP / Three.js with Motion in the same component tree.
- Apply grain / noise exclusively to fixed `pointer-events-none` pseudo-elements.
- Z-index restraint: do not spam `z-50`. Use systemic scale (sticky nav, modals, overlays, grain).

## Stack (when greenfield)

- Framework: React or Next.js. Default Server Components. Wrap providers in `"use client"`.
- Styling: Tailwind v4 default (`@tailwindcss/postcss` or Vite plugin). v3 only if existing project demands it.
- Interactivity isolation: motion components MUST be isolated leaves with `"use client"`.
- State: local `useState`/`useReducer`. Global ONLY for deep prop-drilling avoidance (Zustand, Jotai, Context).
- Never `useState` for continuous values (mouse position, scroll). Use `useMotionValue` / `useTransform` outside React render cycle.
- Icons: Phosphor / HugeIcons / Radix / Tabler (priority). Lucide on explicit user request only.

## Dark Mode Protocol (Section 8)

- Dual-mode by default. Never ship light-only or dark-only without explicit instruction.
- Pick token strategy: Tailwind `dark:` variant OR CSS variables. One strategy per project.
- Contrast parity across modes: if a CTA pops in light, it pops in dark.
- No pure `#000000` or pure `#ffffff`. Off-black (zinc-950, near-black warm gray) and off-white.
- Respect `prefers-color-scheme: dark` unless brand insists otherwise.

## Out of Scope (Section 13)

Taste-skill is NOT for:
- Dashboards / dense product UI / admin panels (use Fluent, Carbon, Atlassian, or Polaris).
- Data tables (use TanStack Table or AG Grid).
- Multi-step forms / wizards.
- Code editors (use Monaco / CodeMirror).
- Native mobile (use Apple HIG / Material directly).
- Realtime collab UIs.

For those surfaces, apply ONLY the marketing-page / about-page / landing-page parts where applicable.

## Pre-Flight Check (Section 14)

Before shipping, run the full ~50-item matrix in SKILL.md §14. Every box must honestly pass. If a single checkbox cannot be ticked, the page is not done.